text: Thryptomene caduca is a shrub species in the family Myrtaceae that is endemic to Western Australia. The shrub is found in a small area in the Gascoyne region of Western Australia between Shark Bay and Northampton where it grows in sandy soils. ==References== caduca Category:Endemic flora of Western Australia Category:Rosids of Western Australia Category:Vulnerable flora of Australia Category:Plants described in 2014 Category:Taxa named by Barbara Lynette Rye Category:Taxa named by Malcolm Eric Trudgen
